  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Trying to verify our contract on arbitrum testnet, it fails displaying the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\nverifying ClearingHouseLogic (0x4602af97388bCc1e2249e3bbF012F9217359c5A4) ...\r\nwaiting for result...\r\nFailed to verify contract ClearingHouseLogic: NOTOK, Fail - Unable to verify\r\n{\r\n  \"apikey\": \"XXXXXX\",\r\n  \"module\": \"contract\",\r\n  \"action\": \"verifysourcecode\",\r\n  \"contractaddress\": \"0x4602af97388bCc1e2249e3bbF012F9217359c5A4\",\r\n  \"sourceCode\": \"...\",\r\n  \"codeformat\": \"solidity-standard-json-input\",\r\n  \"contractname\": \"contracts/protocol/clearinghouse/ClearingHouse.sol:ClearingHouse\",\r\n  \"compilerversion\": \"v0.8.13+commit.abaa5c0e\",\r\n  \"licenseType\": 14\r\n}\r\nEtherscan sometime fails to verify when only metadata sources are given. See https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/9573. You can add the option --solc-input to try with full solc-input sources. This will include all contract source in the etherscan result, even the one not relevant to the contract being verified\r\n```\r\n\r\nNot sure what is the reason, tried with `hardhat etherscan --network arbtest  --solc-input`, it failed with another error which makes sense, our repo contains a lot of code.\r\n\r\n```\r\nverifying ClearingHouseLogic (0x4602af97388bCc1e2249e3bbF012F9217359c5A4) ...\r\ncontract ClearingHouseLogic failed to submit : \"NOTOK\" : \"Source code exceeds max accepted (500k chars) length\" [object Object]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. git clone https://github.com/rage-trade/perpswap-contracts\r\n2. yarn install\r\n3. yarn etherscan --network arbtest ",
